 Yes indeedy, these are exciting times indeed! I mean, a few months ago, all we had was the prospect of A\BOX to be released in the future sometime, and possibly 'Amiga compatible' PIOS/pOS machines. With Quikpak turning our machines into high-end toasters...  

Now the move to PowerAmiga is here - and owned by a company with some money, who will hopefully do the Amiga some good for once! In the articles section, I've done four different articles condering the four main developments in Amiga future at the moment - Gateway 2000 / Amiga International; Phase 5; PIOS/ProDad; and Direct's PowerAmiga. So the Amiga's dead? I could be writing about how £2500 will buy you a QuikPak PC/Amiga machine with P150 and '060 (or worse still, how to get your Amiga software running under UAE on a PC). But I'm not. 
	----------------------------------------
 @{"b"}Amiga Graffiti?@{"ub"}  

There I was, doing my Economics exam, and there I cast my eye over the desk. Amongst the 'TF 4 AG' and 'Man Utd are Crap', I see, would you believe it: 'Amiga 1200's Rule, PCs are Crap'. Wahey! And as I looked around, I saw the entire desk (while, quite a bit of it) was sporting a PC vs Amiga debate. The level was not exactly high, with the only pro arguments being 'Rule', and the only anti arguments being 'are Crap'. It was about Digitiser level, actually. But it was reassuring as I scribbled a few supply and demand curves in the last five minutes, to glance over my paper and see 'Amiga Rules' staring back at me.  

Incidentally, someone had also written 'IBM Rule'. Is that a pro-PC comment, or anti-Windoze (considering OS2 Warp)? I should have created similar confusion by writing 'Gateway 2000 Rule'...  

But really, looking at it, I reckoned the Amiga people had written their comments first, as the PC comments were in response, so it shows how Amiga users like to shout out their beliefs. Could this be the start of a new craze? Sitting in a bog to see 'PPC 4 Amiga' scrawled on the cubicle, or maybe 'Hands off Viscorp, she's Gateway's now'. Maybe wandering in some alleyway to see a nice 'Intel Outside' logo spray-painted on the wall ;) 
